      "rationale": "All primary model inputs characterized with documented uncertainty bounds: blood viscosity (2.8–3.5 mPa·s, literature range), geometric tolerances (±0.05 mm per manufacturing specification), inlet flow waveform (±10% amplitude, clinical measurement uncertainty). A comprehensive Monte Carlo analysis propagating these bounds through 10,000 model evaluations confirmed that the 95th-percentile RH remains below 1.0. Input uncertainty quantification is assessed as meeting gradation 2 requirements."
